{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a64417cc3fb48d65ff8", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 60, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "EM", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9d"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b6488", "title": "JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "Hysteresis loops for two magnetic materials&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;are given below:<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/7fe27fbf-137c-478b-9e86-8a79eb4fe2c1-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 228px;\" /><br />These materials are used to make magnets for electric generators, transformer core and electromagnet core. Then it is proper to use:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "pUmWl", "text": "<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;for transformers and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math></p><p>for electric generators.</p>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "qCI75", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;for electromagnets and transformers.", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "O5mv0", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;for electric generators and transformers.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ryBC6", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;for electromagnets and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> for electric generators.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>As we know that, area of&nbsp;Hysteresis loop represents the net loss of energy&nbsp;by the material per unit volume,taken over complete cycle.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/d8351c41-e7db-42cd-8a5f-6d86920cd3e7-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 223px;\" /><br />Graph <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is hard ferromagnetic material substance as the area of the loop is more, hence the hysteresis loss will be more and thus the value of coercivity will be high which are best suited to use as Permanent Magnet<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/f2d12aad-bfdc-4da9-a7ab-a04b96dbc02a-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 218px;\" /><br />Graph <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;is graph of soft ferromagnetic material substance as the area of the loop is less and hence the hysterisis loss will be less which is required condition for transformer. And the value of coercivity will be low too.</p><p>Hence this material are best suited to use as Electromagnets and Transformer.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ15493590", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ce